text.tspan: Literacy rates vs. average years of schooling, 1970 to 2010
The vertical axis measures literacy rates for population aged 15 and older, according to UNESCO estimates
combining different measurement methodologies. The horizontal axis measures average number of years of total
schooling across all education levels, for the population aged 15-64.
Adult literacy rate, population 15+ years, both sexes (%)
Source: World Bank, Lee and Lee (2016)
